I am confused -- I don't think our version is vulnerable, but I can't check, because it's not actually tied to a dependabot alert.

If we do need to upgrade to sidekiq 7, we will first need to upgrade the version of redis installed on our boxes.  We have redis 4, but sidekiq 7 requires at least redis 6 through its new dependency on the redis-client gem.  If not, you get this error:

```
redis-client requires Redis 6+ with HELLO command available
```
